Aquarius Platinum and Lonmin Could Move: South Africa Stock Market Preview

-- B y   L a u r e n   v a n   d e r   W e s t h u i z e n
-- 
2011-04-27T22:01:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-27/aquarius-platinum-lonmin-south-african-equity-preview.html
The following stocks may rise or
fall in  South Africa  today. Symbols are in parentheses and
prices are from the last close. Yesterday was a public holiday
in South Africa.  The FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index rose 9.29, or 0.03
percent, to 32,668.15 in Johannesburg on April 26.  Aquarius Platinum Ltd. (AQP)  : The world’s fourth-largest
producer of the metal releases its third-quarter earnings. The
shares were unchanged at 38 rand.  Lonmin Plc (LON)  : The world’s third-largest platinum
producer said the E1 shaft at its Marikana mine in South Africa
has reopened after a fatal accident on April 12 halted
operations. The stock price declined 15.70 rand, or 0.9 percent,
to 181.51 rand.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Lauren van der Westhuizen in  Cape Town  at 
 lvanderwesth@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Reed Landberg at 
 landberg@bloomberg.net . 